Women are gatvol and they are taking extra measures. On Saturday, young and old women embarked on a self-defense
class. The session was in partnership with Black Board Africa
and the International Kenbu Kai Karate (IKKO), held in Market Theatre in
Joburg. They told Daily Sun it was time they defended
themselves against men. They said they are afraid following the recent spate
of gender-based violence against women and children. Imtiaz Abdulla, founder of IKKO urged woman never to
say sorry to an attacker during a self-defense. He encouraged them that self-defense should be a
lifestyle. kids how to fight back when they are getting snatched. 